Program: Outlook
Title: 20/05/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p007m8x7
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 21 May 2010
Oil Spill Fisherman Vietnamese-American Thuong Nguyen has a tattoo on his arm saying "Life is difficult". He's one of many Louisiana fishermen left devastated by the oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico - he was only just getting back on his feet after Hurricane Katrina struck in 2005. He talks to Outlook about his struggles in the past, and fears for the future. Everest summitteer 22 year old Bonita Norris has just become the youngest British woman to reach the summit of Mount Everest. But until a year ago, she had never climbed a mountain. From base camp, she tells Matthew Bannister what it's like to stand on top of the world's highest mountain, and the difficulties she faced in her descent. Zambia's First Lady In our continuing series on Africa's first ladies, Veronique Edwards from the BBC African Service talks to Thandiwe Banda, wife of Zambian president Rupiah Banda. Show less